Sparkling Water ridden by jockey S'manga "Bling" Khumalo wins the 2022 edition of the Durban July horse race in Durban, on July 2, 2022. AFP/RAJESH JANTILAL DURBAN - Filly Sparkling Water won the Durban July's main race at the Greyville race course. It looked like a close run affair going into the final stretch but jockey Smanga Khumalo found an extra gear to take Sparkling Water clear of the competition. WATCH | Crowds gallop back to Greyville The filly, trained by Mike de Kock, went on to take first place. Jet Dark finished second with Safe Passage completing the top three. Defending champion Kommetdieding finished fifth this time.